If the customers can't park,they find another store,and I'm out of business.

261
00:17:13,190 --> 00:17:15,900
I just don't know where else to go,here it's safe.

262
00:17:16,360 --> 00:17:18,820
Oh,I know a place.

263
00:17:18,820 --> 00:17:22,840
over there at,uh,fairmount park at the,uh,sweet briar cutoff.

264
00:17:25,190 --> 00:17:27,810
Uh,don't let the looks of me stop you.

265
00:17:27,810 --> 00:17:31,380
it ain't the ritz,but you're not going to be there long anyway.

266
00:17:32,250 --> 00:17:35,000
You're onto sunnier shores real soon.

267
00:17:35,000 --> 00:17:37,030
you're one of the lucky ones.I can tell.

268
00:17:37,030 --> 00:17:39,160
I can tell.

269
00:17:42,640 --> 00:17:44,500
thank you.

270
00:18:01,100 --> 00:18:03,610
here.For you.

271
00:18:05,230 --> 00:18:09,060
you're all alone.To grow old protect yourself.

272
00:18:10,310 --> 00:18:12,910
- I can't take that.
- You have to.

273
00:18:13,350 --> 00:18:15,710
Think about your girls.

274
00:18:15,710 --> 00:18:18,070
Everybody needs a helping hand.

275
00:18:30,690 --> 00:18:32,850
land of plenty?

276
00:18:33,740 --> 00:18:36,180
Not for people like marlene.

277
00:18:36,180 --> 00:18:37,800
So who was this homeless dude?

278
00:18:37,800 --> 00:18:40,060
Name's hopper.A regular.

279
00:18:40,330 --> 00:18:42,160
Came in for his daily lottery ticket.

280
00:18:42,160 --> 00:18:44,590
You said fairmount park at sweet briar?

281
00:18:44,590 --> 00:18:46,340
Definitely.

282
00:18:46,340 --> 00:18:49,870
That's where marlene's body was found.

283
00:18:52,180 --> 00:18:54,190
Well,canvas struck out.

284
00:18:54,190 --> 00:18:57,340
Hard to believe anybody would stick around here for eight years.

285
00:18:58,100 --> 00:19:00,060
I thought will was coming with.

286
00:19:00,060 --> 00:19:01,870
Had something to do.

287
00:19:01,870 --> 00:19:04,300
- Like what?
- Wouldn't say.

288
00:19:06,800 --> 00:19:08,740
Vincent hopper?

289
00:19:08,740 --> 00:19:10,620
Philly P.D.

290
00:19:10,920 --> 00:19:14,410
Wanted to talk to you about a woman named marlene bradford?

291
00:19:14,410 --> 00:19:17,690
Her body was found near here in the lake.

292
00:19:20,710 --> 00:19:22,790
she didn't deserve that.

293
00:19:22,790 --> 00:19:25,920
One in a million,that marlene.Nicest kids.

294
00:19:25,920 --> 00:19:28,470
You directed her here back in '99.

295
00:19:28,590 --> 00:19:32,090
I thought we'd be celebrating our move to sunnier shores together.

296
00:19:32,340 --> 00:19:34,980
Well,looks like she wasn't the only one who didn't make it.

297
00:19:35,830 --> 00:19:37,630
Ah,run of bad luck.

298
00:19:37,630 --> 00:19:39,670
Put me behind schedule.

299
00:19:39,790 --> 00:19:41,740
You're lucky I'm still here.

300
00:19:41,740 --> 00:19:44,000
There's a change around the corner,you know?

301
00:19:46,490 --> 00:19:49,000
You know something about marlene's disappearance?

302
00:19:49,200 --> 00:19:51,660
Marlene wasn't meant for the streets.

303
00:19:52,300 --> 00:19:55,140
Last time I saw her,it was only getting worse.

304
00:20:10,370 --> 00:20:12,010
Nat,you're supposed to be in the car with abby.

305
00:20:12,010 --> 00:20:14,490
I got to use the john if you don't mind.

306
00:20:14,490 --> 00:20:16,540
You couldn't have taken her with you?

307
00:20:16,640 --> 00:20:19,640
Jeez,can't I even take a pee without her?

308
00:20:20,880 --> 00:20:23,660
And anyway,she's sound asleep.

309
00:20:29,550 --> 00:20:32,220
ah,she's just being a teenager.

310
00:20:32,520 --> 00:20:35,250
she's better than most of them around here.

311
00:20:35,880 --> 00:20:37,730
You know everybody here,don't you?

312
00:20:37,730 --> 00:20:40,300
After a few years,it gets easy.

313
00:20:40,730 --> 00:20:42,470
Years?

314
00:20:42,690 --> 00:20:45,000
But that's not going to be you.

315
00:20:46,730 --> 00:20:49,560
It's abby's birthday tomorrow.

316
00:20:51,550 --> 00:20:54,110
I can't even get her a cake.

317
00:20:54,140 --> 00:20:56,170
Here.

318
00:20:59,200 --> 00:21:01,010
It's a hope ticket.

319
00:21:01,010 --> 00:21:03,020
A hope ticket?

320
00:21:03,020 --> 00:21:06,230
Lets you dream about what you'd do with the winnings.

321
00:21:06,570 --> 00:21:09,150
A million dollars.

322
00:21:09,810 --> 00:21:12,930
Deal is,if you win,you got to share the wealth.

323
00:21:12,930 --> 00:21:14,840
50-50.

324
00:21:15,090 --> 00:21:17,480
Think of it as a finder's fee.

325
00:21:20,240 --> 00:21:22,480
What would you do with a half a million dollars?

326
00:21:22,480 --> 00:21:24,910
Oh,I'd get my family back.

327
00:21:25,930 --> 00:21:28,270
Half a mill?

328
00:21:28,270 --> 00:21:31,840
I could provide for my boy and his mom.

329
00:21:31,840 --> 00:21:34,490
Like I should.

330
00:21:40,570 --> 00:21:42,600
How old were you in this picture?

331
00:21:42,600 --> 00:21:45,900
My son's got his eye set on this special glove.

332
00:21:47,650 --> 00:21:49,920
and I mean to get it for him.

333
00:21:56,430 --> 00:21:58,010
Then I'm sure you will.

334
00:21:58,010 --> 00:21:59,800
- Mom! 
- What's the matter?

335
00:21:59,800 --> 00:22:01,600
гн The car,it's gone.
гн What?!

336
00:22:01,600 --> 00:22:03,380
- Where's abby?
- I don't know,mom!

337
00:22:03,380 --> 00:22:06,160
- Where's your sister?
- She was in the car!

338
00:22:09,980 --> 00:22:12,160
The car disappeared with abby in it?

339
00:22:13,490 --> 00:22:15,830
Guess she wasn't so lucky after all.

340
00:22:16,160 --> 00:22:18,440
That happened the night before marlene was murdered.

341
00:22:18,440 --> 00:22:20,190
So,what did marlene do?

342
00:22:20,190 --> 00:22:22,980
What any mother would do.
She panicked.

343
00:22:42,070 --> 00:22:44,930
whoa.Scared the crap out of me,buddy.

344
00:22:46,380 --> 00:22:48,590
Just closing up.

345
00:22:49,390 --> 00:22:50,970
You need something?

346
00:22:50,970 --> 00:22:53,680
Winter of '95 was really something.

347
00:22:55,030 --> 00:22:56,580
Yeah,it was.

348
00:22:56,580 --> 00:22:58,510
Can't get it out of my mind.

349
00:22:58,510 --> 00:23:01,370
Yeah,right.Well,you know,I-I should finish closing.

350
00:23:01,510 --> 00:23:04,260
My wife was killed that night.

351
00:23:04,260 --> 00:23:06,410
Hit-and-run trucker.

352
00:23:07,000 --> 00:23:09,660
But you know that,don't you?

353
00:23:11,470 --> 00:23:13,960
- No. 
- She didn't die right away.

354
00:23:13,960 --> 00:23:16,320
- Oh,please.
- Took a while.

355
00:23:16,940 --> 00:23:18,450
Please.I-I...

356
00:23:18,450 --> 00:23:21,730
what-what-what do you...want?Money?A-anything.

357
00:23:21,730 --> 00:23:24,870
What do you think you can possibly give me?

358
00:23:24,870 --> 00:23:26,950
I-I don't know.I...

359
00:23:26,950 --> 00:23:29,250
- you left her there to die.
- Please.It was an accident.

360
00:23:29,250 --> 00:23:31,450
You drove away.

361
00:23:32,670 --> 00:23:35,380
- Close your eyes.
- No.Please-don't do this.

362
00:23:35,820 --> 00:23:39,930
- Please.
- I said,close your eyes.

363
00:23:47,530 --> 00:23:51,330
No child abduction reports filed the night
marlene's station wagon went missing.

364
00:23:51,330 --> 00:23:53,910
Car wasn't even reported stolen.

365
00:23:54,060 --> 00:23:57,570
Doesn't make sense.
Losing a kid-- parent's worst nightmare.

366
00:23:57,770 --> 00:23:59,470
Do almost anything to get them back.

367
00:23:59,470 --> 00:24:01,350
So why not file a report?

368
00:24:01,350 --> 00:24:03,190
Maybe marlene knew who stole it.

369
00:24:03,190 --> 00:24:06,150
Or maybe she got spooked.
Cops could start asking questions.

370
00:24:06,150 --> 00:24:08,440
Like what was abby doing alone in the car in the first place?

371
00:24:08,440 --> 00:24:11,320
- Single mother living on the streets.
- State could take both girls.

372
00:24:11,640 --> 00:24:12,710
Easily.

373
00:24:12,710 --> 00:24:15,550
But her kid's missing.
Think it's a chance she'd take.

374
00:24:16,680 --> 00:24:19,700
The car was at a public park.
Lot of restrictions.

375
00:24:19,950 --> 00:24:21,160
Yeah?

376
00:24:21,290 --> 00:24:23,290
What if it got towed?

377
00:24:29,350 --> 00:24:31,220
Marlene bradford.

378
00:24:31,220 --> 00:24:34,020
Her car got towed november '99,by you.

379
00:24:35,030 --> 00:24:37,150
Fellas,you know how many cars I tow?

380
00:24:37,150 --> 00:24:39,720
Her car had a kid in it.
That ring any bells?

381
00:24:39,720 --> 00:24:42,540
According to the records,marlene racked up over $200 in fines.

382
00:24:42,540 --> 00:24:44,670
And she didn't have that kind of dough.

383
00:24:45,650 --> 00:24:47,780
But somehow she got her wheels back.

384
00:24:49,470 --> 00:24:51,570
Like I said,I don't remember.

385
00:24:52,450 --> 00:24:54,210
Look,bro...

386
00:24:54,510 --> 00:24:57,020
I've waived a few tickets in my day.

387
00:24:57,020 --> 00:24:59,460
And they weren't nearly as hot as marlene.

388
00:24:59,460 --> 00:25:02,260
You remember that,uh,,red camaro?

389
00:25:02,260 --> 00:25:05,650
Oh.She stripped a few gears.

390
00:25:06,220 --> 00:25:08,100
I bet you fellas get over a lot,huh?

391
00:25:08,100 --> 00:25:09,390
Eh,yeah.

392
00:25:09,390 --> 00:25:11,650
- Job don't pay nothing,huh?
- Gotta make it up somehow.

393
00:25:11,650 --> 00:25:12,880
Yeah,damn right.

394
00:25:12,880 --> 00:25:14,890
That what happened with marlene?

395
00:25:15,000 --> 00:25:16,580
You cut her a deal?

396
00:25:16,580 --> 00:25:18,650
Yeah,you could say that.

397
00:25:19,360 --> 00:25:21,770
Hey,nothing comes for free,if you know what I mean.

398
00:25:34,860 --> 00:25:37,590
mommy is so sorry,baby.

399
00:25:37,590 --> 00:25:40,180
I promise I'll never leave you like that again.

400
00:25:40,790 --> 00:25:45,120
I knew you'd come get me 'cause tomorrow's my birthday.

401
00:25:45,800 --> 00:25:48,510
It's amazing you'll even be alive to see it.

402
00:25:48,510 --> 00:25:50,540
- Natalie... 
- what?

403
00:25:50,540 --> 00:25:53,370
- And she could've been killed,mom.
- You don't think I know that?

404
00:25:54,720 --> 00:25:57,960
Just go inside,where it's warm,

405
00:25:57,960 --> 00:26:01,200
while I go talk to the driver.

406
00:26:04,960 --> 00:26:07,960
All right,it's going to be $279.

407
00:26:08,890 --> 00:26:10,990
I get paid tomorrow.Maybe I could come...

408
00:26:10,990 --> 00:26:13,850
look,save it.
You want your ride tonight,lady,you pay for it.

409
00:26:13,850 --> 00:26:15,270
No,you don't understand.

410
00:26:15,270 --> 00:26:18,890
If I don't get this car out of here,
my kids don't have anywhere to sleep tonight.

411
00:26:19,140 --> 00:26:21,520
That's not my problem,lady.

412
00:26:25,300 --> 00:26:27,260
Look...

413
00:26:27,260 --> 00:26:30,080
I got something in the car.

414
00:26:30,080 --> 00:26:32,460
You could get a lot of cash for it.

415
00:26:32,460 --> 00:26:35,280
- Like?
- A gun.

416
00:26:38,070 --> 00:26:40,430
it's right here.

417
00:26:45,820 --> 00:26:48,380
it was right here!It was right here!

418
00:26:48,380 --> 00:26:50,710
You stole it!

419
00:26:51,040 --> 00:26:53,290
Look,you want your ride or not?

420
00:26:53,370 --> 00:26:56,850
I can't leave here without it.My girls...

421
00:27:06,170 --> 00:27:08,700
other ways to settle that tab,lady.

422
00:27:08,700 --> 00:27:10,400
What?

423
00:27:13,370 --> 00:27:16,300
we've got nowhere else to go,please.

424
00:27:17,210 --> 00:27:19,180
Mom?

425
00:27:19,690 --> 00:27:22,130
what's taking so long?

426
00:27:23,320 --> 00:27:25,750
just go back inside,baby.

427
00:27:28,070 --> 00:27:30,450
I'll be there in a minute.

428
00:27:46,410 --> 00:27:48,840
hey,what the he?

429
00:27:52,390 --> 00:27:53,980
her kids were in the next room.

430
00:27:53,980 --> 00:27:56,090
- You took the gun,too,didn't you?
- That's crazy.

431
00:27:56,090 --> 00:27:57,890
It didn't just walk away,dirtbag.

432
00:27:57,890 --> 00:27:59,630
Hey,it was that girl.

433
00:27:59,630 --> 00:28:01,850
- What girl?
- The one that was in the car.

434
00:28:01,850 --> 00:28:04,800
Look,I saw her take something out of the glove box that night.

435
00:28:05,270 --> 00:28:07,730
Abby took the gun?

436
00:28:10,200 --> 00:28:12,380
Time to stop pretending you don't remember,abby.

437
00:28:12,380 --> 00:28:13,310
I'm not pretending.

438
00:28:13,310 --> 00:28:15,130
Certain things you don't forget...

439
00:28:15,130 --> 00:28:17,180
like being in a car that's getting towed.

440
00:28:17,180 --> 00:28:19,480
And taking the gun that killed your mom.

441
00:28:19,550 --> 00:28:21,590
I got scared.

442
00:28:21,690 --> 00:28:24,810
I saw the tow truck driver,and I grabbed it.

443
00:28:25,360 --> 00:28:27,730
What about after?

444
00:28:30,680 --> 00:28:32,940
Dangerous-- having a gun in close quarters like that.

445
00:28:32,940 --> 00:28:34,390
Maybe it went off accidentally.

446
00:28:34,390 --> 00:28:37,130
Maybe you got tired of your mother's empty promises.

447
00:28:37,130 --> 00:28:40,890
- They weren't empty promises.
- You were living in a car,abby.Come on.

448
00:28:41,110 --> 00:28:42,770
My mom did her best.

449
00:28:42,770 --> 00:28:46,150
Everything she did was for us.

450
00:28:47,690 --> 00:28:50,290
Only natalie didn't see it.

451
00:29:06,020 --> 00:29:10,230
- promise not to tell mom?
- Whatever,stop being a baby.

452
00:29:12,660 --> 00:29:14,720
- What are you doing with that?
- It was in the glove box.

453
00:29:14,720 --> 00:29:16,040
It's not a toy,abby!

454
00:29:16,040 --> 00:29:18,160
I wasn't playing with it!I...

455
00:29:20,270 --> 00:29:22,650
there must be,like,50 cans in there.

456
00:29:22,650 --> 00:29:25,170
We hit the jackpot tonight,girls.

457
00:29:28,300 --> 00:29:30,170
How much will we get for these?

458
00:29:30,170 --> 00:29:31,640
Lots.

459
00:29:31,640 --> 00:29:34,060
Guess what we're going to do with the money?

460
00:29:34,060 --> 00:29:36,040
Something for my birthday?

461
00:29:36,040 --> 00:29:37,600
Something special.

462
00:29:37,600 --> 00:29:39,280
Like what?

463
00:29:39,280 --> 00:29:42,140
Some cake you got out of the garbage?

464
00:29:42,380 --> 00:29:44,680
Natalie,please.

465
00:29:45,300 --> 00:29:47,560
So how did you get the car back?

466
00:29:50,610 --> 00:29:53,080
I sold the gun.

467
00:30:04,930 --> 00:30:07,350
I know what you did.

468
00:30:07,350 --> 00:30:10,650
- I'll get us out of this.
- How?

469
00:30:11,060 --> 00:30:13,680
By showing us houses we're never going to live in?

470
00:30:13,680 --> 00:30:16,390
We're better off without you and your stupid fantasy world.

471
00:30:16,450 --> 00:30:18,950
- Stop it,natalie.
- You're disgusting!

472
00:30:18,950 --> 00:30:21,120
- I hate you!
- You don't mean that.

473
00:30:21,120 --> 00:30:23,630
I wish it was you that died instead of dad.

474
00:30:28,460 --> 00:30:30,020
Nat,

475
00:30:30,490 --> 00:30:33,270
I'm sorry,baby!

476
00:30:33,270 --> 00:30:34,700
Natalie!

477
00:30:34,700 --> 00:30:36,460
Natalie,come back!

478
00:30:36,460 --> 00:30:38,970
Nat!

479
00:30:40,120 --> 00:30:43,130
Natalie!

480
00:30:49,300 --> 00:30:52,510
natalie loved mom.
She didn't mean it.

481
00:30:52,510 --> 00:30:54,660
But she left with the gun.

482
00:30:54,660 --> 00:30:57,600
And the next night your mom was dead.

483
00:31:08,220 --> 00:31:10,040
Hey,john.

484
00:31:10,040 --> 00:31:11,850
Come on in.

485
00:31:14,870 --> 00:31:17,560
You haven't picked up your phone all day.

486
00:31:21,450 --> 00:31:23,650
All this time...

487
00:31:23,650 --> 00:31:26,630
he wasn't what I imagined.

488
00:31:26,630 --> 00:31:28,850
What did you do,will?

489
00:31:28,850 --> 00:31:32,300
I followed him into the alley.

490
00:31:32,920 --> 00:31:35,990
It was dark,raining.

491
00:31:36,580 --> 00:31:38,420
Go on.

492
00:31:40,060 --> 00:31:42,980
I put my gun to his chest.

493
00:31:46,860 --> 00:31:49,680
But I couldn't do it.

494
00:32:02,200 --> 00:32:05,310
I wanted him to be a monster.

495
00:32:05,310 --> 00:32:07,270
But he wasn'T.

496
00:32:07,270 --> 00:32:11,330
He was just a guy in a diner.

497
00:32:15,440 --> 00:32:17,360
I thought...

498
00:32:17,360 --> 00:32:20,250
if I could do it...

499
00:32:20,890 --> 00:32:23,670
it would make it better.

500
00:32:25,410 --> 00:32:28,090
It won'T.

501
00:32:30,800 --> 00:32:33,710
You did the right thing.

502
00:32:35,290 --> 00:32:37,540
That night at dink's,

503
00:32:37,540 --> 00:32:39,890
they were playing miles davis,

504
00:32:39,890 --> 00:32:41,990
her favorite.

505
00:32:42,700 --> 00:32:44,950
I...

506
00:32:45,180 --> 00:32:48,580
haven't played one of his records since.

507
00:32:49,280 --> 00:32:52,470
It's been 12 years.

508
00:32:55,230 --> 00:32:57,500
A long time,will.

509
00:32:57,500 --> 00:33:00,660
Yeah,it feels like yesterday.

510
00:33:06,070 --> 00:33:10,550
She's not coming back,is she,john?

511
00:33:12,330 --> 00:33:14,950
No,she's not.

512
00:33:44,160 --> 00:33:47,130
Things got ugly with you and your mom.

513
00:33:48,220 --> 00:33:51,200
"I hate you.
Wish you were dead."

514
00:33:51,840 --> 00:33:52,860
Harsh words.

515
00:33:52,860 --> 00:33:55,320
I was a kid.Kids mouth off.

516
00:33:55,500 --> 00:33:58,280
Difference is,you had the gun that killed her.

517
00:33:59,180 --> 00:34:02,100
You got something to say,say it.

518
00:34:02,200 --> 00:34:05,150
At 14,it all seemed so black and white.

519
00:34:05,150 --> 00:34:07,440
Life sucks because you have a lousy mother.

520
00:34:07,440 --> 00:34:09,820
What do you know about it?

